cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with a problem in computer vision (zero-shot learning) and proposes a new method that combines multiple embedding spaces for classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as ensembling and calibration, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of semantic information and text descriptions indicates a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with multi-modal data, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
